cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about deep learning-based visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses network architecture, network training, and network objective, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also evaluates the performance of visual tracking methods on various benchmarks, which involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with video analysis and processing, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
